Actually the procedure is start the motor and loosen the adjuster until 
you hear the clatter. Tighten 'til it stops. Tighten 3/4 additional 
turn. (Small block Chevy hydraulics are the easiest valves in the world 
to adjust. Messy though....)

Jim

